        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 25 at 2:45PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 245 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
western Colorado Springs, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Northwestern Colorado Springs, Air Force Academy, Manitou Springs,
and Cascade.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
